> What is the tent channel on split buses? I have a bay, so I guess I don't have
> this. Is this going to make a major difference with the way it seals to the
> bus? I would like to have a good seal around the bus for sure.

It's a piece of aluminum with a "c" on the end. Part of the tent is
inserted in the C that has a cord inside and holds it tight. I really
don't have any good pictures of it, but it is bolted right to the
body. Works great!
 
> I have been wondering a little about the flat ceiling part of the tent that
> connects to the bus. Like you said, it looks like water would pool there.

it does, but not a real big deal. just something I noticed.
 
> The part of the tent that connects to the bus, does it come up to the bottom
> of the sliding door or is it just open to the underneath of the bus? I have a
> little one that will immediately crawl under the bus if give the chance :)

just open. 

